{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17491107","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17491107"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T05:32:55+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T05:32:55+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"833"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"833","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/833"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.06,0.18,0.07,0.34,0.35]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"833"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"43000"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"833","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/833"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"833"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"27982"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"19"},{"type":"tags","id":"35"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"78"},{"type":"tags","id":"315"},{"type":"tags","id":"1155"},{"type":"tags","id":"4959"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"11644"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"673"},{"type":"contributions","id":"1619"},{"type":"contributions","id":"16482"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44486"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44926"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"43000","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/43000"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 67-year-old man presents with a six month history of a painless swelling on the right side of his face. He has a thirty pack-year smoking history and drinks three cans of beer a day. On examination the patient has a droop at the right corner of his mouth and there is a 3 cm diameter, well circumscribed swelling immediately anterior to the right tragus. On palpation the lesion is firm and mobile, with no apparent tethering to the overlying skin. A number of greasy, dark skin lesions over the posterior neck and back are also noted.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Epidermoid cyst","Metastatic deposit from a melanoma","Metastatic deposit from a bronchogenic neoplasm","Pleomorphic adenoma of the parotid","Parotid adenocarcinoma"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe parotid space contains both the parotid gland and external carotid artery, as well as the intra and extraparotid lymph nodes, retromandibular veins and extracranial branches of the facial nerve.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe majority of pathologies related to the parotid space arise from the parotid gland, and may be benign or neoplastic in nature. Perhaps the commonest cause of such a swelling in the parotid region would be a pleomorphic adenoma of the parotid. Physical examination of pathologies in this region is often non-specific, however this patient has evidence of facial asymmetry and this would be consistent with a facial nerve problem. The facial nerve passes through the superficial and deep part of the parotid gland. Whilst a very large adenoma could cause compression of the facial nerve, it is likely that there is involvement of the nerve in a malignant process. Thus a \u003Cstrong\u003Eparotid adenocarcinoma\u003C/strong\u003E is the most likely diagnosis. Whilst many advanced tumours may have spread to adjacent tissues, making the mass less mobile or fixed, early spread of a centrally-placed tumour is likely to have spread and involved the facial nerve as it passes through the gland.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EMetastatic deposits do occur within the parotid gland, however are significantly less common than primary tumours of the parotid gland. Certainly lesions such as melanoma must be considered - but the greasy, dark lesions on this patient\u0027s back and neck are seborrhoeic keratoses and not melanomas.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Facial nerve weakness in the presence of a swelling in the parotid region indicates malignancy until proven otherwise."],"references":["Kanekar S, Mannion K, Zacharia T, Showalter M. Parotid Space. Otolaryngologic Clinics of North America. 2012;45(6):1253-1272."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"27982"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"833"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"27982","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/27982"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-02-27T17:39:44+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-10-13T22:55:40+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"833"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"43000"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"19","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/19"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udd2a","name":"General Surgery","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:47:20+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"2"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"35","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/35"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc43","name":"Otorhinolaryngology","synonyms":["ENT","HEENT"],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-01-16T08:40:48+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"2"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"64","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/64"},"attributes":{"emoji":